quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,70,"They said, "
  2,71,"He [Mûsâ (Moses)] said, "
  2,72,"And (remember) when you killed a man and fell into dispute among yourselves as to the crime. But Allâh brought forth that which you were hiding."
  3,10,"Verily, those who disbelieve, neither their properties nor their offspring will avail them whatsoever against Allâh; and it is they who will be fuel of the Fire."
  3,11,"Like the behaviour of the people of Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) and those before them; they belied Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.). So Allâh seized (destroyed) them for their sins. And Allâh is Severe in punishment."
  3,12,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) to those who disbelieve: "